snippet.textDisplay: It was funny that you said you could use that big pan as a weapon. My grandmother heard a noise one night so she got up and eased her way into the kitchen in the dark, and she could see a man climbing in the window, so she grabbed her castiron skillet and she whacked him in the head and knocked him back out the window. lol. She said the street light was just enough so that she could see him laying on the ground, so she went and called the police but the guy was gone when they got there, but he was caught at the hospital about an hour later. He went there because he had a 5-inch gash in his head that was exposing his skull. So after he was there for a couple of days and treated for his wound and a concussion, he was taken to jail. He tried saying it wasn't him that was breaking into her house, but he was found guilty because he left behind about a pint of DNA. lol.

snippet.textDisplay: Hello you three! You're doing an amazing job entertaining and educating others! I love you. Although, I do have to say, when the spoon was tossed in the crib for fun, I shuddered. I've seen a baby about Lenny's  age topple over with a spoon in his mouth and fall on it! Horrible. Choking, the spoon had to be grabbed at multiple times (it was almost down his throat!) and could have choked him to death in front of us. Luckily it was plucked out on the third attempt and the baby almost passed out and adults were started to scream and cry. Horrible! Please, please, please don't ever leave him standing with a spoon. So dangerous if you aren't around!! Thank you! Blessings!
